{"type": "article", "id": 41737, "title": "觉得自己是手残党？一定是你的工具没用对！｜这个设计了不起", "description": "我们每天都为你推荐几个最近发现的好设计。", "date": "2017-06-07T22:56:50Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 39455, "name": "Art. Lebedev Studio"}, {"id": 41230, "name": "Llun"}, {"id": 41231, "name": "Dossofiorito"}, {"id": 41232, "name": "Dow Design"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 9, "praise_count": 170, "image": "img/article/article_show/201706072144170BUsricCxg374VbM.jpg", "contents": "<p nocleanhtml=\"true\">        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} p.p3 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} </style>  </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。</p><h3>Perfect Cut by Polarlab</h3><p>来自台湾的 Polarlab 是一个由 DIY 爱好者创立的设计团队，为了让更多人体验到手工的乐趣，他们耗时一年多的时间开发了这套名为 Perfect Cut 的美工刀和辅助工具。美工刀采用了圆柱形的特制刀身，减轻了长时间持握对手指造成的压迫感，而且左右手都可以使用。致力于让手残党也能切出各种形状的工具模组包含了三用切割尺、45 和 90 度角的专用辅助尺、可以一手拿美工刀一手扶住材料切出完美圆弧的圆规刀以及一个自由调整斜切角度的模块。这是它的<a href=\"https://www.zeczec.com/projects/perfectcut\" rel=\"nofollow\">众筹链接</a>，售价从 1490 新台币起。<br></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214452UzyvpZoPl7tdwSuR.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.563077\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214452WxEnH930AgkcbVpT.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666250\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214458u79SpRFMc3wkItxi.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562674\" data-format=\"gif\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214548vdqnjwtE3CbIhlDy.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562602\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214452R3zyiCXUYf5a6A8d.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.936923\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Paperclips Collection by Llun</h3><p>来自土耳其的 Llun 是一个由设计师 Efil Türk 创立的品牌，这套纸夹是她以常见于土耳其 Kilim 手工编织地毯中的几个图案为灵感设计的，可以作为书页的最佳点缀。你可以通过<a href=\"https://llun.co/projects/paperclips-collection/\" rel=\"nofollow\">链接</a>购买，售价从 14 美元起。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201706072146148RPlFV4kaA7wJTQX.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666406\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214614qL7nYH2Sf34VA5Xl.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214614B3prEaJlVZkvQR4I.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201706072146145v3LXtz24lRqGhgJ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: inherit; font-family: Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, 冬青黑, STXihei, 华文细黑, &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;, 微软雅黑, SimSun, 宋体, Helvetica, Tahoma, &quot;Arial sans-serif&quot;; font-size: 20px; text-align: left;\">The Phytophiler by Dossofiorito</span></h3><p>如果你厌倦了中规中矩的花器，来自意大利设计工作室 <a href=\"http://dossofiorito.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Dossofiorito</a> 的 The Phytophiler 系列花盆或许会让你重新审视我们和植物的互动方式。与各种配件组合在一起的手作陶罐被赋予了艺术装置的气息，人们可以通过镜子观察花草或是利用延伸在外的花盆打造一个迷你丛林。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214819SuwQknZvMNsEmbaJ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.665625\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214819zVeUbm5MgxFlGh0Q.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.665625\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214819hCM5HRnNbslSiz0F.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.665625\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Fontanus-1 by Art. Lebedev Studio</h3><p>街边的饮水站也可以拥有艺术气息。最近，俄罗斯设计工作室 <a href=\"https://www.artlebedev.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Art. Lebedev Studio</a> 就带来了一个名为 Fontanus-1 的概念饮水站，它的外观或许会让你误以为这仅仅是一个黑色的装饰雕塑。除了顶部 C 字型的出水口以外，柱身上还特意留有为小朋友和宠物准备的出水口，让不同群体各取所需。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214639elofwndUQmPs6xij.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214639Ffj5ObntDSHg2oWU.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.867619\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201706072146394guaNhOVKRx7rHJe.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.120952\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Juices by Dow Design Ltd</h3><p>长大之后，在街边的杂货铺看到小时候最爱的棒冰，你有没有因为包装显得低龄化而失去购买的欲望？在新西兰，类似的问题也同样困扰着希望扩大消费群的水果冰沙品牌 Juices，为此他们委托设计公司 <a href=\"http://dowdesign.co.nz/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Dow Design</a> 设计了一套简约风的包装。纯文字和透明包装袋的搭配强调了“天然”、“无添加”的概念，纸盒也采用了相同的设计风格——和配有卡通插画的前代相比，要更“老少皆宜”。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214656MZKeRA72YnwVWiy5.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.643000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214657Bgi34xzAmuZW8l9w.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.643000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201706072146570aMhLixtYXApGjBn.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.728000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214657i7jg819ePdkxMpha.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.643000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>C-Stunners by Cyrus Kabiru</h3><p>来自肯尼亚的 <a href=\"http://www.ckabiruart.daportfolio.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Cyrus Kabiru</a> 是一名自学成才的艺术家，由于父母拒绝为他配置眼镜，他自年幼时就开始在家乡内罗毕的街头寻找金属和其他废弃物品，搭建看起来相当前卫的眼镜。随着阅历增长，他开始有意识地将科幻作品和魔幻写实主义与非洲传统的元素相结合，颠覆传统眼镜的造型，创作了一系列夸张且充满未来感的饰品。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214723IDueYjCmhriM1bAs.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.250305\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214723ob04XcCzkOrVnq7I.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.246883\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214724Bb3AG624li5xayQw.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.001182\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170607214723faN6BzJ1yK7iRDPh.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.001182\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201706072147242giOf1h6dRotVyv0.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.250000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}